<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 02 at 11:22PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Snow Showers producing visibility of a mile or less at times...
At 1114 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking a line of snow showers
extending from 18 miles northeast of White Sulphur Springs to 6
miles east of Montana City. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.
These snow showers could result in slick roads and visibility
dropping to a mile or less at times.
Locations impacted include...
White Sulphur Springs, East Helena, Montana City, Fort Logan On The
Smith River, Newlan Creek Reservoir, Winston, Checkerboard, Fort
Logan and Goose Bay.
&amp;&amp;</description>
